y%20That%20Has%20Split%20Scientists%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ECould%20lumpy%20metallic%20rocks%20in%20the%20deepest%2C%20darkest%20reaches%20of%20the%20ocean%20be%20making%20oxygen%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20sunlight%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20scientists%20think%20so%2C%20but%20others%20have%20challenged%20the%20claim%20that%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bdark%20oxygen%26quot%3B%20is%20being%20produced%20in%20the%20lightless%20abyss%20of%20the%20seabed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20--%20detailed%20last%20July%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature%20Geoscience%20--%20called%20into%20question%20long-held%20assumptions%20about%20the%20origins%20of%20life%20on%20Earth%2C%20and%20sparked%20intense%20scientific%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20were%20also%20consequential%20for%20mining%20companies%20eager%20to%20extract%20the%20precious%20metals%20contained%20within%20these%20polymetallic%20nodules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearchers%20said%20that%20potato-sized%20nodules%20could%20be%20producing%20enough%20electrical%20current%20to%20split%20seawater%20into%20hydrogen%20and%20oxygen%2C%20a%20process%20known%20as%20electrolysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20cast%20doubt%20on%20the%20long-established%20view%20that%20life%20was%20made%20possible%20when%20organisms%20started%20producing%20oxygen%20via%20photosynthesis%2C%20which%20requires%20sunlight%2C%20about%202.7%20billion%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDeep-sea%20discovery%20calls%20into%20question%20the%20origins%20of%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Scottish%20Association%20for%20Marine%20Science%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release%20to%20accompany%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDelicate%20Ecosystem%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnvironmentalists%20said%20the%20presence%20of%20dark%20oxygen%20showed%20just%20how%20little%20is%20known%20about%20life%20at%20these%20extreme%20depths%2C%20and%20supported%20their%20case%20that%20deep-sea%20mining%20posed%20unacceptable%20ecological%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGreenpeace%20has%20long%20campaigned%20to%20stop%20deep%20sea%20mining%20from%20beginning%20in%20the%20Pacific%20due%20to%20the%20damage%20it%20could%20do%20to%20delicate%2C%20deep%20sea%20ecosystems%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20environmental%20organisation%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20incredible%20discovery%20underlines%20the%20urgency%20of%20that%20call%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20was%20made%20in%20the%20Clarion-Clipperton%20Zone%2C%20a%20vast%20underwater%20region%20of%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%20between%20Mexico%20and%20Hawaii%20of%20growing%20interest%20to%20mining%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScattered%20on%20the%20seafloor%20four%20kilometres%20(2.5%20miles)%20beneath%20the%20surface%2C%20polymetallic%20nodules%20contain%20manganese%2C%20nickel%20and%20cobalt%2C%20metals%20used%20in%20electric%20car%20batteries%20and%20other%20low-carbon%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20that%20gave%20rise%20to%20the%20dark%20oxygen%20discovery%20was%20partly%20funded%20by%20a%20Canadian%20deep-sea%20mining%20business%2C%20The%20Metals%20Company%2C%20that%20wanted%20to%20assess%20the%20ecological%20impact%20of%20such%20exploration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20sharply%20criticised%20the%20study%20by%20marine%20ecologist%20Andrew%20Sweetman%20and%20his%20team%20as%20plagued%20by%20%26quot%3Bmethodological%20flaws%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMichael%20Clarke%2C%20environmental%20manager%20at%20The%20Metals%20Company%2C%20told%20AFP%20that%20the%20findings%20%26quot%3Bare%20more%20logically%20attributable%20to%20poor%20scientific%20technique%20and%20shoddy%20science%20than%20a%20never%20before%20observed%20phenomenon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScientific%20Doubts%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESweetman's%20findings%20proved%20explosive%2C%20with%20many%20in%20the%20scientific%20community%20expressing%20reservations%20or%20rejecting%20the%20conclusions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20July%2C%20five%20academic%20research%20papers%20refuting%20Sweetman's%20findings%20have%20been%20submitted%20for%20review%20and%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20did%20not%20present%20clear%20proof%20for%20his%20observations%20and%20hypothesis%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Matthias%20Haeckel%2C%20a%20biogeochemist%20at%20the%20GEOMAR%20Helmholtz%20Centre%20for%20Ocean%20Research%20in%20Kiel%2C%20Germany.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20questions%20remain%20after%20the%20publication.%20So%2C%20now%20the%20scientific%20community%20needs%20to%20conduct%20similar%20experiments%20etc%2C%20and%20either%20prove%20or%20disprove%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOlivier%20Rouxel%2C%20a%20geochemistry%20researcher%20at%20Ifremer%2C%20the%20French%20national%20institute%20for%20ocean%20science%20and%20technology%2C%20told%20AFP%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%20no%20consensus%20on%20these%20results%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDeep-sea%20sampling%20is%20always%20a%20challenge%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20it%20was%20possible%20that%20the%20oxygen%20detected%20was%20%26quot%3Btrapped%20air%20bubbles%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20measuring%20instruments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20sceptical%20about%20deep-sea%20nodules%2C%20some%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20years%20old%2C%20still%20producing%20enough%20electrical%20current%20when%20%26quot%3Bbatteries%20run%20out%20quickly%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20is%20it%20possible%20to%20maintain%20the%20capacity%20to%20generate%20electrical%20current%20in%20a%20nodule%20that%20is%20itself%20extremely%20slow%20to%20form%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20contacted%20by%20AFP%2C%20Sweetman%20indicated%20that%20he%20was%20preparing%20a%20formal%20response.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20types%20of%20back%20and%20forth%20are%20very%20common%20with%20scientific%20articles%20and%20it%20moves%20the%