g%20me%20along%20to%20a%20friend%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20Seoul%20who%20needed%20a%20teacher.%20Without%20much%20agency%2C%20I%20fell%20in%20line.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20apartment%20was%20nestled%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20rundown%20alley.%20It%20was%20small%2C%20musty%2C%20and%20filled%20with%20sterile%20fluorescent%20light.%20The%20new%20town%20was%20on%20the%20very%20outskirts%20of%20an%20expanding%20metropolis%2C%20the%20last%20stop%20on%20the%20newest%20subway%20line.%20To%20fill%20the%20time%2C%20I%20signed%20up%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-taekwondo-strips-putin-of-black-belt-invasion-of-ukraine-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efor%20taekwondo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20evenings.%20I%20was%20the%20only%20adult%20in%20a%20dojo%20full%20of%20small%20children%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20I%20taught%20during%20the%20day.%20It%20was%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D7t8xwpW8gJQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20episode%20of%20Seinfeld%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20where%20Kramer%20takes%20karate.%20I%20Skyped%20home%20often%20from%20dark%20and%20smoky%20PC%20bangs%20(internet%20caf%C3%A9s)%20to%20connect%20to%20the%20people%20who%20knew%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-of-loneliness-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20lonelier%20than%20I%20had%20ever%20been%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Then%20I%20met%20the%20Kims.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220e291d38-e9b6-4b87-bd18-afc9126808bb%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20asked%20me%20to%20teach%20their%20daughter%20English%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20owned%20the%20restaurant%20at%20the%20end%20of%20my%20alley.%20It%20was%20called%20The%20Pig%20House%20and%20served%20exactly%20what%20you'd%20expect%20from%20a%20restaurant%20with%20that%20name.%20Winding%20aluminum%20ducts%20snaked%20down%20like%20tentacles%20to%20the%20grills%20at%20each%20table.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20day%2C%20a%20woman%20approached%20me.%20It%20was%20a%20friend%20of%20theirs%20who%20spoke%20English%20who%20said%20the%20Kims%20asked%20if%20I%20would%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-online-tutor-wealthy-kids-how-make-learning-fun-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etutor%20their%20daughter%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Eujin%2C%20who%20was%20six.%20I%20agreed.%20I%20gave%20Eujin%20lessons%20on%20the%20heated%20floor%20of%20a%20small%20room%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20restaurant%2C%20often%20while%20her%20dad%2C%20Byungdong%2C%20watched%20Korean%20soap%20operas%20beside%20us.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESoon%2C%20I%20was%20having%20dinner%20there%20most%20nights%20after%20taekwondo.%20Eujin's%20mom%2C%20Myungjoo%2C%20bought%20an%20English%20phrase%20book%20that%20she%20used%20as%20a%20tool%20in%20our%20nightly%20conversations.%20Once%2C%20frustrated%20with%20each%20other%20and%20eager%20to%20practice%20English%2C%20I%20witnessed%20an%20argument%20using%20the%20book.%20Myungjoo%20searched%20for%20the%20right%20insult.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BTalking%20to%20you%20is%20like%20talking%20to%20a%20brick%20wall%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20over-enunciated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EByungdong%20grabbed%20the%20book%2C%20flipping%20pages%20for%20the%20proper%20retort.%20A%20full%20minute%20passed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20know%20what%20you%20are%20talking%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20clapped%20back%2C%20his%20face%20contorting%20as%20it%20always%20would%20when%20he%20tried%20to%20pronounce%20English%20words.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cc2b5a19-90ed-42fa-ab27-e4210ed2c2cd%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20were%20what%20I%20needed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20relationship%20deepened.%20They%20took%20me%20to%20noraebangs%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkaraoke-inventor-whose-bad-singing-launched-global-music-culture-dies-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ekaraoke%20rooms%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20with%20their%20extended%20family.%20I%20spent%20Chuseok%2C%20Korean%20Thanksgiving%2C%20with%20them.%20On%20weekends%2C%20sometimes%20we%20would%20pile%20into%20Byungdong's%20taxi%20and%20go%20hiking%20in%20places%20I%20never%20would%20have%20found.%20Other%20times%20I%20took%20them%20into%20Seoul%20to%20explore%20the%20neighborhoods%20I%20was%20discovering%20because%20they%20rarely%20went%20into%20the%20city.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20realized%20throughout%20all%20of%20this%20my%20loneliness%20was%20melting%20away.%20But%20it%20was%20more%20than%20that.%20As%20an%20only%20child%20of%20a%20divorced%20family%2C%20spending%20time%20with%20the%20Kims%20was%20like%20therapy%20I%20never%20knew%20I%20needed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20left%20Korea%20after%20seven%20months%20but%20never%20lost%20contact%20with%20the%20Kims.%20Today%2C%20Eujin%20is%2024%2C%20the%20age%20I%20was%20when%20we%20met.%20I%20have%20kids%20of%20my%20own%20who%20are%20roughly%20the%20ages%20she%20and%20her%20brother%20Woonghee%20were%20back%20then.%20Eujin's%20English%20is%20great%2C%20and%20we%20Skype%20regularly.%20She%20sends%20my%20kids%20Christmas%20gifts.%20I%20give%20her%20interview%20advice.%20We%20talk%20about%20the%20Squid%20Game%20and%20share%20recipes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Kims%20want%20to%20come%20to%20the%20US%2C%20and%20we've%20told%20them%20they%20will%20always%20have%20a%20place%20to%20stay.%20After%20all%2C%20that's%20what%20family's%20for.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.